						               													<description>A geography trivia game.  The object of the game is to be the first player to collect 12 Golden Geo Awards.  You win the Geo Awards by answering questions correctly.  You lose the Geo Awards by answering questions incorrectly.  The GeoBee cards have two types of trivia questions--&amp;quot;novice&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;experienced&amp;quot;--to accommodate players ages 8 and up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a turn you use the popping dice randomizer then move your pawn the indicated number of spaces.  If you land on a GeoBee, True/False, or Explore space, you will have to answer one of the respective question cards.  To answer a trivia question on an &amp;quot;Explore&amp;quot; card, you must point to one of the continents or water bodies (river, sea, ocean) on the board as the answer to the question.  If you land on a space occupied by another player(s), you read one of the GeoBee questions and they need to answer it.  If you land on a star space you get a free Golden Geo Award, and if land on a Tourist space, you get a card that might be good or bad.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
